cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about multi-label image recognition, which is a task in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel model based on Graph Convolutional Networks (GCN), which is a popular technique in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL). Therefore, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, such as word embeddings, to represent the object labels. Therefore, cs.CL is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on two multi-label image recognition datasets, which are related to multimedia (MM) applications. Therefore, cs.MM is the least likely sub-category.
